18:10 Local Time, 12:40 GMT, 18:10 IST: Mumbai vs Gujarat is the Western Derby that would be earmarked as a marquee game from here on. Hardik Pandya was a homegrown talent at MI. But he left MI and led Gujarat to two finals, winning one and losing one. He is back at MI. But the Rohit Sharma fans and a few experts aren't pleased. Rohit has won five titles with MI but his removal from captaincy wasn't taken that well by a majority of the MI fans. So, Hardik against his former team finds himself in a soup. But that's what IPL does. It puts you in a spot. Hello and welcome to game 5 of the IPL.

Shubman Gill, the leading run-getter of the previous season, is GT's new captain. It's a new challenge for the stylish batter as he doesn't have much experience as a leader. However, there will still be a lot of eyeballs on how he leads the side. Another future Indian captain in the making? Time will tell. The top three wicket-takers all were from Gujarat in IPL 2023 but they'll be without their spearhead - Mohammed Shami - who has been ruled out of this competition. No Hardik and Shami, those are two massive holes to fill. It'll also be interesting to see which four overseas players make it to the XI. Rashid Khan and David Miller are highly likely to make it. One frontline bowler should also feature - Spencer Johnson or Noor Ahmad or Joshua Little. The other spot will be the toughest decision for the team management. Will they play the experienced Kane Williamson who offers a lot of stability to the batting or will they be tempted to pick Azmatullah Omarzai, the talented all-rounder?

Mumbai Indians too have been dealt with some injury blows. Jason Behrendorff and Dilshan Madushanka are out of this season with Luke Wood and Kwena Maphaka replacing them. Suryakumar Yadav will miss today's match and even Gerald Coetzee is doubtful. Despite all that, they have a strong batting line-up and their pace attack is the stronger suit in the bowling department. Tim David will be the finisher with the bat and MI's template generally has been to play two overseas bowlers. Let's see what their gameplan is this time around. Mumbai are usually slow starters - 11 consecutive defeats in their first match of the season. Can the five-time IPL champions reverse that trend?
JUST IN: Three GT players receive their caps - Spencer Johnson, Omarzai and Umesh Yadav!

Pitch Report | Ian Bishop and Brian Lara: "Looks a beautiful playing surface. 63 metres, 66 metres square boundaries, 73 metres downtown. Six-hitting ground. It's a bit bare in the middle, green patches as well. It's an even surface, some cracks, but this is full of runs. The batters are going to enjoy."
Mumbai Indians have won the toss and have opted to field

Hardik Pandya: We are gonna bowl first. Looks like a decent track, might get better if the dew arrives. Feels good to be back. My birthplace is Gujarat, a lot of success came in Gujarat, very grateful to the crowd and this state. My cricketing birth happened in Mumbai, so really good to be be back. It's been almost two weeks, we started the camp. Boys are very eager to go out there and perform. We had wonderful practice matches and practice nets. All are looking good. The excitement is a different feeling. We have four quicks, three spinners and seven batters. Making sure all the departments are looked after.

Shubman Gill: Feels very excited, to be able to captain at a stadium where I have a lot of fond memories. This has been one of our strengths, the last couple of seasons the support that we've got from the fans has been tremendous for us. I was here a week prior before this game, played a practice match, had a couple of practice sessions. Everyone is looking good, everyone is looking fit. We have got three players making debuts for GT - Umesh bhai, Spencer and Omarzai. There are so many players who will be making their debut later this season. There is Sushant from the U-19s, Sai Sudharsan has been doing well for us in the last couple of sessions.
